{
  "doc_id": "38065",
  "text": "HIV infection can cause a non-inflammatory, mostly sensory neuropathy [CITATION_1] which can also be caused by antiretroviral therapy. In addition, GBS or chronic neuritis/CIDP type neuropathy as well as chronic necrotizing PNS vasculitis leading to a multiplex mononeuropathy can occur in conjunction with HIV infection [CITATION_2] . Other viral infection, especially with hepatitis C, can be associated with necrotizing PNS vasculitis [CITATION_3] .",
